Summary of eeg_lst information.

Source: R/out.R
summary.eeg_lst.Rd

It's also possible to extract the elements by accessing it as a list.

# S3 method for eeg_lst
summary(object, ...)

Arguments

object

An eeg_lst object.

...

additional arguments affecting the summary produced.

See also

Other summary functions: count_complete_cases_tbl(), eeg_ica_cor_tbl(), eeg_ica_summary_tbl(), eeg_ica_var_tbl(), summaries

Examples


summary(data_faces_ERPs)
#> # EEG data:
#> # Sampling rate: 500 Hz.
#> # Size in memory: 181 Kb.
#> # Total duration: 00:00:00.
#> # Summary of segments
#>    .recording n_segments n_incomplete
#>        <char>      <int>        <int>
#> 1: faces.vhdr          2            0
#> # Summary of events
#> Empty data.table (0 rows and 3 cols): .type,.description,n
